title: 11/10: Week 10 Recap - Backfield Tandems to Sort Out (Fantasy Football Podcast)
description:
It was a weird Week 10 with Saquon Barkley's one rushing yard, Cooper Kupp's catchless game, Drew Brees' home struggles and more oddities. We react to the weirdness and then get into the Best of Week 10 (7:32) with another great Daniel Jones Fantasy performance, three more Aaron Jones TDs, Derrick Henry's big game and an O.J. Howard sighting! ... Getting into the big news (16:28) and the early Waiver Wire as Brian Hill and J.D. McKissic could be in line for big work. And then we give Winners (21:05) like Ronald Jones and Damien Williams and Losers (28:40) like Calvin Ridley and David Johnson. And we make sure to touch on the backfield battles (34:45) in CLE, NO and BUF ... Recapping every game (41:00) with a "Believe it or Not" from Heath. Is Odell Beckham about to be great? Can Josh Allen keep this up? Are John Brown, Sammy Watkins and Curtis Samuel flexes at best? ... Email us at fantasyfootball@cbsi.com

itunes:author: CBS Sports, Fantasy Football, Rookies, Rankings, Waiver Wire
itunes:subtitle: The backfield tandems were the big story entering Week 10, so let's take a look at those situations after Sunday's games. And let's talk winners, losers, top performers and Waiver Wire.
